From Creamer Media in Johannesburg, this is the Real Economy Report. Sashnee Moodley: Construction academy Tjeka Training Centre, based in Randfontein, is poised for the training and upskilling of future construction industry artisans, according to the centre. While the anticipated infrastructure boom is yet to happen, Creamer Media journalist Simone Liedtke finds out what the centre is all about. Simone Liedtke: While the Tjeka Training Centre is intended to focus on construction training, something South Africa is in dire need of as the industry itself is in an embattled position, CEO Frans Toua gives us a little more insight. Tjeka Training Matters CEO Frans Toua: Simone Liedtke: Turning more towards the Covid-19 pandemic, he talks us through some of the measures the centre has had to impose, following instructions and regulations as set out by government. Tjeka Training Matters CEO Frans Toua: Simone Liedtke: Toua further also elaborates on what the centre’s focus will be on, moving forward, referring specifically to an increased focus on SMMEs ahead of the anticipated infrastructure boom. Tjeka Training Matters CEO Frans Toua: Sashnee Moodley: That’s Creamer Media’s Real Economy Report. Join us again next week for more news and insight into South Africa’s real economy. Don’t forget to listen to the audio version of our Engineering News daily email newsletter.